html:
Verb[edit]

iacuistī

  1. second-person singular perfect active indicative of iaceō
    1. "you have lain prostrate, you lay prostrate, you have lain down, you lay down; you have reclined, you reclined"
    2. "you have lain ill, you lay ill, you have been sick"
    3. "you have lingered, you lingered, you have tarried, you tarried"
    4. "you have been placed or situated, you have lain, you lay"
    5. "you have been low, flat or level"
    6. "you have lain still, you lay still"
    7. "you have lain dead, you lay dead"
    8. "you have lain in ruins, you lay in ruins"
    9. "you have hung down loose, you hung down loose"
    10. (of the face or eyes) "you have been fixed on the ground, you have been cast down"
    11. "you have been indolent, idle or inactive"
    12. "you have lain dormant or abandoned, you lay dormant or abandoned, you have been of no avail"
    13. "you have lain overthrown, you lay overthrown; you have been refuted; you have been despised"
    14. (of speech or language) "you have been languid, dull or lifeless"
